{
  "stem": "7093.8",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I perhaps just should say that I worked-- I, I eventually got a job at the [INAUDIBLE] library, where I worked for four and a half years with material on the Holocaust mainly.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then I, I got a job with the [INAUDIBLE] Institute for [INAUDIBLE] endeavors, Overseas Development Institute, which was the only time-- I worked there twice, two periods-- the only time when I've worked in a non-Jewish institute.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I loved it, by the way.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was wonderful.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was highly interesting.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then I, I got a job at University College, London.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I have no qualifications whatsoever.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I tried to get a librarianship qualification.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But after my first exams, when I have gained just-- when my teacher thought I was his best pupil and I managed to scrape through-- I decided that I had enough.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I eventually was appointed-- I was in charge of all the Jewish material at University College, two libraries plus an, plus an archive, plus helping out with other Jewish archives, and was recognized as a fully-qualified university librarian without having a piece of paper.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And that's how I finished off eight years ago.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And then I sat down and wro-- started writing my book.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, to, to, to meet Franz.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "To meet Franz yes, certainly yes-- because that, I, I saw things very-- I, I felt that everything was hopeless, that my life was always-- every time I got a little bit up, then bang, I got down again.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I had to start again.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I mean, the finer points I didn't bring in, because I can't.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
